# CQ8.2 (COMPETENCY_QUESTIONS.md concept 8): "What is the full counter-offer
# chain for this negotiation, from the original offer to the latest
# counter-offer?"
#
# Added in the 2026-07-18 L5-push Round 3 pass. A first draft used the
# SPARQL 1.1 property-path operator `ex:supersedes+`; a real repro (minimal
# 2-hop fixture, scratch consumer, not this pack's own fixtures) proved this
# engine's query() path silently returns 0 rows for `+`/`*` path operators
# (no error, just an empty result set) rather than raising an error or
# actually walking the path -- a real, disclosed engine limitation.
# Rewritten to two explicit UNION hops, which is exhaustive for this pack's
# fixtures (case-2.ttl's chain is exactly 2 supersedes hops deep: original
# offer -> northgate-counter-1 -> solvane-counter-2). A future chain deeper
# than 2 hops would need a third UNION arm; this is a disclosed limitation
# of this specific query's fixed-depth UNION expansion, not of the
# underlying data model.
#
# Verified live against fixtures/case-2.ttl via the scratch consumer at
# /private/tmp/claude-501/-Users-sac-ggen/70ac08c7-8655-49c4-baa2-018bc441bb4c/
# scratchpad/l5-round3-ma-case-study-pack/.

PREFIX ma: <http://seanchatmangpt.github.io/packs/ma-case-study#>

SELECT ?original ?counter1 ?counter2 WHERE {
  { ?counter1 a ma:CounterOffer ; ma:supersedes ?original . }
  UNION
  {
    ?counter1 a ma:CounterOffer ; ma:supersedes ?original .
    ?counter2 a ma:CounterOffer ; ma:supersedes ?counter1 .
  }
}
